parameters: [Sign] Buying fresh fish at high prices--

[Sign] Escapees from the island will be subjected to the
death penalty--Mujou Island Magistrate's Office

The view from here is so beautiful. I would have never seen
this horizon if I hadn't been exiled...
----(One month after Chutarou disappeared from Edo)----

Karin? Are you still sleeping? You didn't even eat half of
the meal I made yesterday.

You've been bedridden ever since... I'm worried about you,
you know? Come on, cheer up, Karin. I even made lots of your
favorite \V[82] So, come on.

(...No matter if I try to cheer her up or get angry, it
might just make things worse. Sigh, what should I do...)

It's only been a month since Chutarou-san disappeared. Maybe
he's traveling all over Japan. He might come back suddenly
tomorrow, you know?

If the house you're living in gets dirty while he's away,
Chutarou-san would be sad too. The whole place is covered in
dust, so how about doing a big clean-up? It might help
change your mood a bit.

I'll bring more food later. Make sure you eat properly next
time. Got it, Karin--
--Oei left the house with the unfinished meal on a tray.

(...If the house is dirty when father comes back, he would
be sad... Oei-san is right, I should clean up.)
Huh...? What's this string doing here...?
--Karin pulled on a string next to a wooden box.

This is... a secret basement? I never knew about this. Did
father make this?
Gasp! A letter...! Could it be from father--!?

--Karin read the letter from Chutarou as if she was
searching for something.

To my daughter Karin--If you are reading this letter, it
seems I was unable to keep my promise. I am sorry.
There's no doubt...! This is Dad's handwriting...

The righteous thief Nezumi Kozou was a disguise I took on.
The money I stole was all distributed to the common people
of Edo. The money here is what I saved from my work as a
construction worker and transporter.

There is enough money saved here to cover our house rent for
about three years. I want you to get by with that. Even if I
cannot return home, do not be sad. Do what you must do. Live
with a smile.

Nakataro's Letter: Oei-dono has been your foster parent.
Without her, both you and I might have died. Listen well to
what Oei-dono says, and please grow up healthy. From your
father, Nakataro--

P.S. Next to the desk, I've left a hair ornament and a sword
for you, Karin. Use the hair ornament to throw at an
attacker and escape if necessary. The sword is not meant for
cutting people. Use it without hesitation if it's for the
right cause--

(Dad's hair ornament that he left for me... Does it suit me?
I'll always wear it as a charm...)

And so, I trained hard in swordsmanship and physical
techniques, aspiring to become a righteous thief like my
father. I tried to live the same path as him--

If the "Quick Thief Nezumi Komachi" becomes famous... maybe
Dad, who disappeared, will become curious about the identity
of Nezumi Komachi and return to Edo--I believe this, even if
just a little...
<Sound of waves crashing...></Sound of waves crashing...>

(...And as a result, I'm exiled to this island at the edge
of the sea. Life really doesn't go as planned...)

(Surely, things have been going too well for me until now...
That's why I'm paying for it by being sent to such a distant
island from Edo...)
(Sound of waves crashing... Sound of waves crashing...)

I wonder what's written on this stone monument? The
characters are carved so intricately, it's hard to read...

I am the village chief of this Mujou Island. It must be
tough being exiled at such a young age, isn't it?

Yes... I thought it was better than losing my life, but it's
still hard and sad. Oei-san must be worried sick about me
suddenly disappearing...

I understand how you feel. I was born on this island, but
every exile longs for their homeland beyond the horizon...

This gravestone belongs to a military commander who drifted
onto this island long ago. Over 100 years ago, there was a
great war in Mino, and it belongs to one of the defeated
generals...
Wow... It's the grave of someone very important then.

He lived on this Mujou Island for 50 years without ever
being able to return home and passed away here. He must have
had many regrets not being able to return home...
...(Will I also die here in 50 years' time...)

I heard secretly from an official that you were a great
thief in Edo, is that true? You don't look the part though.

Uh... Yes, that's right. I sneaked into the mansion of a
wealthy merchant in Edo and stole a lot... and then...

Oh? You were distributing the stolen money to the common
people of Edo? Quite the spirited young woman for your age.
--! Could it be, has Nezumi Kozo been exiled to this island?

Nezumi Kozo? That's a nostalgic name. I've heard he was a
righteous thief causing a stir in Edo five years ago, but
unfortunately, he has not been sent to this island.
...! Could it be that you are the daughter of Nezumi Kozo?

Yes. I'm searching for my father. But he hasn't come to this
island, has he?

Hmm... Searching for your father is your mission... I hope
you can meet him someday.

Yes, I hope so too. Thank you, village chief. The day is
drawing to a close, so I'll be taking my leave now--

--Karin bowed her head to the village chief and left the
place.

The general who was exiled to this island a hundred years
ago... Thanks to the ship you built, I was able to safely
escape from this island... I truly thank you.

Eh...? Why are you on this island? I'm on a business trip.
Ahahaha...! If you'd like, I can tell your fortune for free.

Defeat the banished criminal boss and his henchmen who come
to your home (becoming submissive will trigger the criminal
boss's event). Talk to the village chief at the stone
monument in the western part of the island. Have a
conversation at Kachou's house, then go to Kisanosuke's
house to get a fishing rod.

Fish for tuna at the southern beach, and listen to
Kisanosuke's story about the white-haired monk. Meet the
white-haired monk and fish for four sea breams as requested
to advance the story. Anyway, let's escape from the island
and return to Edo. Good luck--

Defeat the banished criminal leader and his henchmen who
came to your home (becoming submissive to the criminal
leader triggers a stage event). Talk to the village chief at
the stone monument in the western part of the island. Have a
conversation at Kachou's house and go to Kisanosuke's house
to get a fishing rod.

Fish for tuna at the southern beach, and listen to
Kisanosuke's story about the white-haired monk. Meet the
white-haired monk and progress the story by fishing and
handing over four sea breams as requested. Anyway, let's
escape from the island and return to Edo. Good luck in
battle--
Are we good to go? Shall we head back to Uraga as is?

Heading back? Got it. Make sure you hold onto the ship
properly.

...A letter has arrived from Edo. It seems to be a pardon.
Honestly... as an official, my reputation is completely
ruined. But it's a life that was once at rock bottom and was
reclaimed without giving up. You should cherish it from now
on.

This island is poor and has limited food supplies. There's
very little fertile land to harvest grains. If you don't
want to starve to death, you'd better fish desperately for
something to eat.

--Hey, hey, hey! What happened to you? Weren't you supposed
to have escaped from Mujou Island? Did you come back on
purpose?

The area to the east from there is the exiled criminals'
district. It's run by the head of the exiled criminals, so
make sure you listen to what they say.

You're the only exiles who have escaped from this deserted
island. And I heard you even received a pardon from the
authorities? Everyone on the island is astonished.
Alright, we've arrived. Get off on the island.
Yeah. Once you're here, there's no escaping anyway.
...(I've ended up in such a faraway place...)

Official: Boatman, good work. You're this month's exile,
huh? A woman, that's unexpected. I hear your crime is theft,
is that correct?
...Yes, that's right. My name is Karin.

Hmm. I'll take you to the eastern district for exiles.
Follow me, Karin or whatever your name is.

Exile Leader: I've brought the new exile. Take care of her
living arrangements on this island. I leave the rest to you.

Hehehe. Leave it to me, Mr. Official. I'll make sure the
newcomer learns the rules and manners of the island...
Hehe! A newcomer who's a woman, that's delightful

...(Considering we're exiled, these guys are a cut above
your average villains.)

This island has few women. And to top it off, a young and
beautiful one at that. This is a blessing from heaven

Uheheh! Exactly, boss\I[15] Now girl, introduce yourself to
everyone, will you?

I am called Karin. I came from Edo. I'm... a bit of a
misfit, but please take care of me.

So your name is Karin, huh? I'm the Exile Leader. The
governance of this exile district is all entrusted to me.
Make sure you listen to what I say, got it?

If you don't obey us, you'll suffer the consequences.
Understand?
...Excuse me, I'm hungry. Could I have something to eat?
Oh, tired from the long journey? For now, eat this.

Eh! These tiny shells won't even make a dent in my hunger!
Don't you have any fish or something?

Ahh! Don't be so picky! On this desolate island in the
middle of nowhere, food is precious! If you have a
complaint, I won't hear it, you insolent newcomer!

Boss... there's no need to be so intimidating... she just
arrived on Mujou Island...

Shut up, Kachou! The most important person here is me! Don't
get in front of the Exile Leader!

Hahahaha! If you don't want to be hit, then keep your mouth
shut! Got it?!

What?! You're going to defy me too?! You're just a newcomer
and already so cheeky! Want to be hit?!

Picking on a girl and acting all high and mighty, you're the
worst kind of thug. Next time I'll aim for your crotch. I'm
pretty good at throwing things.

Ouch! What crime did you commit to be exiled to Mujou
Island?

Theft... I did it about ten times. Stole a total of 5000
ry.
What?! You're such a big-time thief?!

That's right. So don't mess with me, okay? Now where will I
be staying?
Grr... There's a hut in the middle of this district.
Thank you. Then I'll be in your care for a while.

...! (That girl, she's underestimating me...! I'll make her
regret this!)
--Karin left the house of the head of the exiled criminals.

Listen to what the exile leader says. And you must
absolutely not go to the Dragon Ascension Pass, understand?
